    <description>Thrombosis events will include acute coronary syndromes, including angina pectoris and myocardial infarction, stroke, including cerebrovascular infarction, cerebral hemorrhage, and transient ischemic attacks, deep vein thrombosis, and pulmonary embolism.</description>
  </secondary_outcome>
